article.description: — Daniel Deaver had a season-high 20 points as Navy defeated Bucknell 73-55 on Friday night.
article.headline: Deaver scores 20 to lead Navy over Bucknell 73-55
article.linkText: Deaver scores 20 to lead Navy over Bucknell 73-55
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- — Daniel Deaver had a season-high 20 points as Navy defeated Bucknell 73-55 on Friday night. John Carter Jr. had 18 points for Navy (10-4, 3-0 Patriot League). Xander Rice had 14 points for the Bison (3-12, 0-3), who have now lost four games in a row. Elvin Edmonds IV added 12 points. Andre Screen had 11 points. Andrew Funk, whose 19 points per game heading into the contest led the Bison, had 8 points on 3-of-11 shooting. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
